{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Widgets are self-contained: we can adapt them while also supporting older versions of our macOS\/iOS’s.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/widgetpreviewcontext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" on SwiftUI previews to display the widget layout.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Do not define your own corner radius in a widget, use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/containerrelativeshape"},{"type":"text","text":" instead:"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct PillView : View {","    var title: Text","    var color: Color","","    var body: some View {","        Text(title)","            .background(ContainerRelativeShape().fill(color))","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"code":"ContainerRelativeShape","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/containerrelativeshape","overridingTitle":"ContainerRelativeShape","isActive":true},{"text":" is a new shape type that will take on the path of the nearest container shape specified by a parent with an appropriate corner radius based on the position of the shape.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"use the ","type":"text"},{"code":".isPlaceholder(true)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier on a preview to display the widget preview (note: ","type":"text"},{"code":".isPlaceholder","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is not available on Xcode 12b1)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"if something should not be replaced by a placeholder, we need to mark it with "},{"code":".isPlaceholder(false)","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"if we want the same view to support multiple widget families\/sizes, we can to so by adding an environment variable for the widget family: "},{"code":"@Environment(\\.widgetFamily) var widgetFamily","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To display a live countdown or similar, use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:)-4k7ab"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:)-56n81"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:style:)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ +2 hours","\/\/ -3 months","Text(event.startDate, style: .offset)","","\/\/ 2 hours, 23 minutes – Automatically updating as time pass","Text(event.startDate, style: .relative)","","\/\/ 36:59:01 – Automatically updating as time pass","Text(event.startDate, style: .timer)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"These date formats will automatically update the view as time passes (without the need of redrawing it): it’s a great way to make your widgets feel alive on the home screen.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Written By","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Written-By"},{"type":"row","columns":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"zntfdr"}]}],"size":1},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Federico-Zanetello","text":"Federico Zanetello"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev"}]}],"size":4}],"numberOfColumns":5},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Missing anything? Corrections? ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference"}]},{"text":"Related Sessions","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Related-Sessions"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10048-Principles-of-great-widgets","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10028-Meet-WidgetKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10034-Widgets-Codealong-part-1-The-adventure-begins","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10035-Widgets-Codealong-part-2-Alternate-timelines","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10036-Widgets-Codealong-part-3-Advancing-timelines","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10041-Whats-new-in-SwiftUI","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10103-Design-great-widgets"],"style":"list","type":"links"},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Legal Notice"}]}]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2024 Apple Inc. All rights reserved.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple.","type":"text"}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10033-build-swiftui-views-for-widgets"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10033-Build-SwiftUI-views-for-widgets","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10033","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (20 min)","type":"reference"}},"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"Build SwiftUI views for widgets","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC20"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Widgets are bite-sized pieces of information from your app that someone can choose to place on their home screen or Today view. Discover the process of building the views for a widget from scratch using SwiftUI. Brush up on the syntax that you’ll need for widget-specific construction and learn how to incorporate those commands and customize your widget’s interface for a great glanceable experience.","type":"text"}],"references":{"zntfdr":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"zntfdr","type":"image","alt":"Profile image of Federico Zanetello"},"https://zntfdr.dev":{"url":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","title":"Blog","identifier":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/text/init(_:)-56n81":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:)-56n81","title":"Date","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:)-56n81","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Date"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 12, Swift 5.3, iOS 14, macOS 11 (Big Sur), tvOS 14, watchOS 7.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WidgetKit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StoreKit Testing"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"title":"WWDC20","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20","kind":"article"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10048-Principles-of-great-widgets":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10048-Principles-of-great-widgets","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Explore the foundations of great widgets by keeping them relevant and customizable. Learn how to keep widgets up to date with timeline entries and TimelineReloadPolicies. Discover how to adapt your widget to different presentation environments and physical location. And lastly, find out how to create customizable widgets that someone can personalize to their liking.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10048-principles-of-great-widgets","type":"topic","title":"Principles of great widgets"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/text/init(_:)-4k7ab":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:)-4k7ab","title":"new","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:)-4k7ab","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"new"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10034-Widgets-Codealong-part-1-The-adventure-begins":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10034-widgets-codealong-part-1-the-adventure-begins","title":"Widgets Code-along, part 1: The adventure begins","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10034-Widgets-Codealong-part-1-The-adventure-begins","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Take your app on a most wondrous adventure to the home and Today screens of iPhone, iPad, and Mac. Grab the starter project and code along with us! We will guide you through the process of creating a widget for your app from start to finish so that you can provide people with beautiful views and glanceable information in an easily-accessible place. Discover how to create a widget project, learn fundamental concepts for widgets and their structure, configure the widget and its provider, and start exploring timeline concepts."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10035-Widgets-Codealong-part-2-Alternate-timelines":{"abstract":[{"text":"Our code-along continues as we help our widget rewrite the future and travel into an alternate timeline. Continue where you left off from Part 1, or traverse time and space and begin with the Part 2 starter project to jump right into the action. Find out how you can integrate system intelligence into your widgets to help them dynamically change at different points during the day and surface the most relevant information. Explore core timeline concepts, support multiple widget families, and learn how to make your widget configurable.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10035-widgets-codealong-part-2-alternate-timelines","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10035-Widgets-Codealong-part-2-Alternate-timelines","kind":"article","title":"Widgets Code-along, part 2: Alternate timelines"},"WWDC20-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDC20-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png","type":"image"},"zntfdr.jpeg":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10041-Whats-new-in-SwiftUI":{"abstract":[{"text":"SwiftUI can help you build better and more powerful apps for iPhone, iPad, Mac, Apple Watch, and Apple TV.  Learn more about the latest refinements to SwiftUI, including interface improvements like outlines, grids, and toolbars. Take advantage of SwiftUI’s enhanced support across Apple frameworks to enable features like Sign In with Apple. Discover new visual effects, as well as new controls and styles. And find out how the new app and scene APIs enable you to create apps entirely in SwiftUI, as well as custom complications and all new widgets.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10041-Whats-new-in-SwiftUI","title":"What’s new in SwiftUI","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10041-whats-new-in-swiftui"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/zntfdr":{"images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg"},{"type":"icon","identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg"}],"type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","title":"Federico Zanetello (332 notes)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Software engineer with a strong passion for well-written code, thought-out composable architectures, automation, tests, and more."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/zntfdr","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"title":"Contributions are welcome!","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions are welcome!","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"title":"WWDC Notes","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","role":"collection","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10028-Meet-WidgetKit":{"abstract":[{"text":"Meet WidgetKit: the best way to bring your app’s most useful information directly to the home screen. We’ll show you what makes a great widget and take a look at WidgetKit’s features and functionality. Learn how to get started creating a widget, and find out how WidgetKit leverages the power of SwiftUI to provide a stateless experience. Discover how to harness your existing proactive technologies to make sure your widget surfaces relevant material. And create a Timeline that ensures your content is always fresh.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10028-Meet-WidgetKit","title":"Meet WidgetKit","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10028-meet-widgetkit"},"WWDC20.jpeg":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDC20.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10103-Design-great-widgets":{"title":"Design great widgets","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10103-Design-great-widgets","type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10103-design-great-widgets","abstract":[{"text":"Widgets elevate timely information from your app to primary locations on iPhone, iPad and Mac. Discover the keys to designing glanceable widgets, developing a strong widget idea, and clearly communicating with content, color, sizing, layout, and typography.","type":"text"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10036-Widgets-Codealong-part-3-Advancing-timelines":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10036-Widgets-Codealong-part-3-Advancing-timelines","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Take your widget to the next level as we embark upon the third and final stage of the widgets code-along. Pick up where you left off in Part 2 or start with the Part 3 starter project to go warp speed ahead. We’ll explore advanced concepts for widgets, timelines, and configuration. Learn how to load in-process and background URLs and link directly to content within your app. And discover how to create multiple widgets that explore different features within your app, as well as making your widget dynamically configurable.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10036-widgets-codealong-part-3-advancing-timelines","type":"topic","title":"Widgets Code-along, part 3: Advancing timelines"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/containerrelativeshape":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/containerrelativeshape","title":"ContainerRelativeShape","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/containerrelativeshape","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ContainerRelativeShape"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc20/10033":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10033","checksum":null,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10033","type":"download"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/text/init(_:style:)":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:style:)","title":"API","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/text\/init(_:style:)","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"API"}]},"https://github.com/zntfdr":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","title":"GitHub","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/widgetkit/widgetpreviewcontext":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/widgetpreviewcontext","title":".previewContent(WidgetPreviewContext(family: .system..))","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/widgetkit\/widgetpreviewcontext","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".previewContent(WidgetPreviewContext(family: .system..))"}]}}}